content: Just announcing there will be some noise on this stream while I test a script that is checking whether the github CI runners are online.
Okay, testing over for now, this appears to work. @Johan Commelin, would you mind taking one offline later and waiting (<=5 minutes) to see if the bot notices?

@Scott Morrison I'll do that later today.

Minor nitpick: Is it possible to rename the bot easily? Because it's more like "CI runner bot" or "uptime bot" instead of "build time bot".
nael seemed to have a problem, so I rebooted it. (This is the VM that handles the bors queue, so we might have to rebors some PRs.)
I've also switched off lena. I'll wait 5 minutes before turning it on again.
Great! That seems to work. I'm restarting lena.
It seems the @ didn't actually produce notifications, however.
I've got all three notifications so far.
@Johan Commelin do I get notified if I do this?

I'm not able to ssh into lena. Here's what ssh -v outputs (with some paths modified):

Then I'm just left waiting without getting a shell.
Perhaps I should the number of times the scripts retries before it reports something is offline. Currently it tries twice, with a 60 second sleep in between.
If you can't pong a ping within 60s, you're a lousy bot, right?

Seriously lena, what is wrong with you? Your siblings are never misbehaving, always quietly doing their jobs. You're always acting up like a rebellious teenager. It's time to grow up, don't you think?
Perhaps testing ssh connectivity is not the issue. I just asked it to reboot.
lane and lena were offline just now; I've just restarted them. @Scott Morrison did the status bot go down or did I just happen to notice before the bot did?
Hmm, looks like it was running. Let me improve the local logging later, so it records timestamps of successful connections.
Looks like this blip caused the latest staging build to fail: https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/runs/3528554965
Are the runners OK? According to GitHub, only three commits are in progress, and 26 are queued, some for 2 hours.

The page I usually check is this one and it looks like all the workers are active there.

The "in progress" list can be a bit misleading since each commit has multiple jobs associated to it, so some commits show up as queued even though one of its jobs is actually in progress.
I can't seem to ssh into nael at the moment. Note that this seems to have caused the latest build failure: https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/runs/3536609973
Looks like nael had another blip that didn't get picked up by the bot: https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/runs/3537399971
It seems like we've been stress-testing the runners today.
Where is the yoyo emoji when you need it?
(or maybe a 5% discrepancy is normal for this sort of thing?)

Kevin Buzzard said:

(or maybe a 5% discrepancy is normal for this sort of thing?)

The timings run on a VM in the cloud, which introduces a ton of noise since other VMs may use the same processor. When I set it up, the noise wasn't so bad, but it has increased a lot recently, to the point where the timings are really only good for a very rough sense of where the compilation times are going (up up and away).
nale is currently offline according to this page. I'll wait a few minutes to see if this bot picks it up and then restart it manually.

I have just restarted the runner on nale.

@Scott Morrison It seems that the bot missed nale being offline for at least 7-8 minutes.

What kind of "offline" is this actually? SSH timeout? https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/settings/actions/runners shows that Lena is dutifully building her PRs. She's also responding to pings.
It might be that she's so busy she doesn't let the SSH server get any cycles?!
That seems to be the most common situation when the runners "go offline"; I can't seem to SSH in (see this message) but ping works.

slightly overloaded indeed:

$ ssh lena.vm.uni-freiburg.de uptime
 18:51:44 up 12 days, 11:39,  0 users,  load average: 30.09, 30.20, 24.88
Is this something we can improve by giving the scheduler some hints?
I think the problem is likely too little RAM. The failure mode looks like the system is swapping so much it can't get any other work done.
Guess we need to fix our CI machines
Feel free to chime in on the secret cabal channel!
But it would be great if could get some extra RAM on the Freiburg machines as well.
I just restarted lane and nela which looked like they were offline. I don't know how long they were down though. It looks like lena is offline but I can't SSH in...
I happened to notice nale was offline, so I just cleared the tmp-* files and restarted the runner.

Looks like the runners are out of space again https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/actions/runs/1342114687 ?
Maybe I'm missing it, but I'm not seeing the "out of space" message in the logs you linked?

OK, I've just gone through and cleared all the temp files from the Freiberg runners (sudo rm /tmp/tmp-*). Hopefully that helps! We may want to automate this since who knows when GitHub will fix the issue, but I can't look into it right now.
I'm getting out of space errors again at https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/actions/runs/1355343749

Hmm, I can't see the oom error in those logs but the "upload precompiled mathlib zip file" seems to be forever stuck with the yellow status. Does GitHub actually show something useful there for you? Or maybe I'm just looking in the wrong place?

lena was offline, so I just restarted it. @Scott Morrison is the bot down?

edit: I also went through the other runners and cleared the temp files just in case.

Hmm... Should I turn this bot off? I can't tell if it is doing anything helpful. I can easily change its reporting criteria if anyone has a suggestion. Currently it saying "offline" if two consecutive attempts to login to an ssh shell (separated by a 60s pause) fail.
The runners are all active at the moment. https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/settings/actions/runners
Would it make a difference if you switch to ping instead of ssh?
Okay, it's using ping -c 1 now. Let's see what happens.
Ideally I think we should be scraping the information at https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/settings/actions/runners, and post here if the status changes to offline.
Do I remember correctly that Azure1 and Azure2 are extremely expensive, and the plan was to disable them once we have enough Hoskinsons?
It should have been formatted as hoskinsons :wink:
lane has died in the middle of multiple PR batches today
I guess it's probably out of memory / disk space?
I can't SSH in, so it's definitely still overloaded, one way or another.
How much work does it add to just nuke these runners from the github UI when this happens, until someone can fix them?
I removed the pr label from lane, it can't be trusted to do anything at all right now
@Scott Morrison The VMs were upgraded to 20G RAM today.
@Jannis Limperg just noting that the benchmark bot hasn't been running since the 8th.
CI is failing for #10350 with "Error: No space left on device".
I wish the self-hosted github runner would clean up the build directories...

#10350 fails linting mathlib, but if I click "details" too see the problem I only see the yellow circle rotating, without any message. Is this a problem of CI or there is something I can do to fix it?
I've tried to re-run all the jobs, but it didn't worked

For some reason, the error only appears on the status page: https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/actions/runs/1562877810
The self-hosted runner: lena lost communication with the server. Verify the machine is running and has a healthy network connection. Anything in your workflow that terminates the runner process, starves it for CPU/Memory, or blocks its network access can cause this error.
Since the runners should be back online, I've set them to re-rerun and see what happens...
I've had the lean-permutation runners betray me twice in https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/actions/runs/2280987158 now
I think nale has dropped maybe 5-10 jobs on me today
It would be great if we had an easy way to tell which runners were failing every time
I've seen a few dropped jobs too, are you sure it's Nale?
At least, I've seen a few dropped without a message and without a log, which I think means the runner is just disconnecting, right?
Yes, I know. The entire department is offline!!!
I'm working on a mobile connection atm.

Error: The log was not found. It may have been deleted based on retention settings.
See e.g. https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/runs/7563120099?check_suite_focus=true (where I expected the build to succeed)
I'm going to go kill this bot.
